README
======================


commandline commands are indicated as follows

`cd WellTempLogger`

DO NOT INCLUDE the `` when typing the commands
Hit enter after typing a command to execute

Notes about the command are indicated with #
DO NOT INCLUDE the Notes when typing the commands

1. open a Terminal.app window
2. `cd` # change directory to the Home folder
3. `cd WellTempLogger` # change directory to the WellTempLogger folder
4. `conda activate welltemplogger` # activate the correct python environment
5. `python wt.py`  # launch the WellTempLogger application
6. Stop the application by using Control+C

Everytime the application successfully launches a new data file is create in the ~/WellTempLogger/data

